            'Luke 22:31–34': '<h3> <span>Luke 22:31-34</span></h3><p><span><sup>31&#xA0;</sup>And the Lord said, <span>&#x201C;Simon, Simon! Indeed, Satan has asked for you, that he may sift <i>you</i> as wheat.</span> </span> <span><sup>32&#xA0;</sup><span>But I have prayed for you, that your faith should not fail; and when you have returned to <i>Me,</i> strengthen your brethren.&#x201D;</span></span></p><p><span><sup>33&#xA0;</sup>But he said to Him, &#x201C;Lord, I am ready to go with You, both to prison and to death.&#x201D;</span></p><p><span><sup>34&#xA0;</sup>Then He said, <span>&#x201C;I tell you, Peter, the rooster shall not crow this day before you will deny three times that you know Me.&#x201D;</span></span></p>'
