            'Matt 4:18–22': '<h3> <span>Matthew 4:18-22</span></h3><p><span><sup>18&#xA0;</sup>And Jesus, walking by the Sea of Galilee, saw two brothers, Simon called Peter, and Andrew his brother, casting a net into the sea; for they were fishermen. </span> <span><sup>19&#xA0;</sup>Then He said to them, <span>&#x201C;Follow Me, and I will make you fishers of men.&#x201D;</span> </span> <span><sup>20&#xA0;</sup>They immediately left <i>their</i> nets and followed Him.</span></p><p><span><sup>21&#xA0;</sup>Going on from there, He saw two other brothers, James <i>the son</i> of Zebedee, and John his brother, in the boat with Zebedee their father, mending their nets. He called them, </span> <span><sup>22&#xA0;</sup>and immediately they left the boat and their father, and followed Him.</span></p>'
